        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 8:41PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 841 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monroeton, or 9 miles southwest of Reidsville, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, McLeansville, Summerfield, Gibsonville, Stokesdale, Haw
River State Park, Lake Guilford Mackintosh Marina, Monticello, Lake
Jeanette Marina, and Altamahaw-Ossipee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
